Subject: Gold color, one more idea.

Hi,

Magnesium needs to be plated to prevent corrosion. If you call your local
plating houses you will find someone that does it. The process has been
around for a long time and does produce a brownish gold sheen on the metal.
The process is a Dow #7  or #9.

